choices.text: the establishment of the United Republic of Tanzania. The United Republic of Tanzania was established on 26 April 1964, when Tanganyika and Zanzibar merged to form a single country. The United Republic of Tanzania is a country in East Africa bordered by Kenya and Uganda to the north, Rwanda, Burundi and the Democratic Republic of the Congo to the west, and Zambia, Malawi and Mozambique to the south. The country's eastern borders lie on the Indian Ocean. The capital city is Dodoma, where the President's Office, the Assemblies of the first and second chambers of parliament, and all ministries are located. Dar es Salaam, the former capital, retains most government offices and is the country's largest city, principal port, and leading commercial centre. Tanzania is a one-party dominant state with the Chama Cha Mapinduzi party in power. From its formation until 1992, it was the only legally permitted party in the country. Elections for president and the National Assembly were last held in October 2015. The CCM holds approximately 75% of the seats in the assembly. The first president of Tanzania, Julius Nyerere, served from 1964 to 1985. The current president is John Magufuli, who took office in November 2015.
